The United States is imposing new sanctions on elements of the Cuban regime responsible for detaining and sentencing individuals who have spoken out against the government. The US stands with the Cuban people and will continue to sanction those who oppress them. The US government is also working to provide internet access to circumvent censorship and reviewing its remittance policy to support the Cuban people. The US embassy in Havana will be restaffed to provide consular services and engage with civil society while ensuring the safety of US diplomats. The US will work with partners in the region to pressure the Cuban regime to release political prisoners, restore internet access, and respect the fundamental rights of the Cuban people.